{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a creative technologist"},{"time":2000,"text":"and the focus of my work is on public installations."},{"time":7000,"text":"One of my driving passions"},{"time":10000,"text":"is this idea of exploring nature,"},{"time":12000,"text":"and trying to find hidden data within nature."},{"time":14000,"text":"It seems to me that there is"},{"time":17000,"text":"this latent potential everywhere, all around us."},{"time":19000,"text":"Everything gives out some kind of data,"},{"time":21000,"text":"whether it's sound or smell or vibration."},{"time":24000,"text":"Through my work, I've been"},{"time":26000,"text":"trying to find ways to harness and unveil this."},{"time":30000,"text":"And so this basically led me to"},{"time":33000,"text":"a subject called cymatics."},{"time":35000,"text":"Now, cymatics is the process of visualizing sound"},{"time":40000,"text":"by basically vibrating a medium such as sand or water,"},{"time":44000,"text":"as you can see there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"So, if we have a quick look at the history of cymatics"},{"time":49000,"text":"beginning with the observations of resonance,"},{"time":51000,"text":"by Da Vinci, Galileo, the English scientist Robert Hook"},{"time":55000,"text":"and then Ernest Chladni."},{"time":57000,"text":"He created an experiment using a metal plate,"},{"time":60000,"text":"covering it with sand and then bowing it"},{"time":63000,"text":"to create the Chladni patterns that you see here on the right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"Moving on from this, the next person to explore this field"},{"time":71000,"text":"was a gentleman called Hans Jenny in the 1970s."},{"time":73000,"text":"He actually coined the term cymatics."},{"time":76000,"text":"Then bringing us into the present day"},{"time":78000,"text":"is a fellow collaborator of mine"},{"time":80000,"text":"and cymatics expert, John Stewart Reed."},{"time":83000,"text":"He's kindly recreated for us"},{"time":85000,"text":"the Chladni experiment."},{"time":87000,"text":"What we can see here is"},{"time":89000,"text":"the metal sheet, this time connected to a sound driver"},{"time":92000,"text":"and being fed by a frequency generator."},{"time":94000,"text":"As the frequencies increase,"},{"time":96000,"text":"so do the complexities of the patterns that appear on the plate."},{"time":99000,"text":"As you can see with your own eyes."},{"time":104000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"So, what excites me about cymatics?"},{"time":111000,"text":"Well, for me cymatics is an almost magical tool."},{"time":114000,"text":"It's like a looking glass into a hidden world."},{"time":118000,"text":"Through the numerous ways that we can apply cymatics,"},{"time":121000,"text":"we can actually start to unveil the substance of things not seen."},{"time":126000,"text":"Devices like the cymascope, which you can see here,"},{"time":128000,"text":"have been used to scientifically observe cymatic patterns."},{"time":132000,"text":"And the list of scientific applications is growing every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"For example, in oceanography,"},{"time":138000,"text":"a lexicon of dolphin language is actually being created"},{"time":141000,"text":"by basically visualizing the sonar beams that the dolphins emit."},{"time":144000,"text":"And hopefully in the future we'll be able to gain some deeper understanding"},{"time":147000,"text":"of how they communicate."},{"time":149000,"text":"We can also use cymatics for healing and education."},{"time":151000,"text":"This is an installation developed with school children,"},{"time":153000,"text":"where their hands are tracked. It allows them"},{"time":155000,"text":"to control and position cymatic patterns"},{"time":157000,"text":"and the reflections that are caused by them."},{"time":160000,"text":"We can also use cymatics as a beautiful natural art form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"This image here is created from a snippet"},{"time":166000,"text":"of Beethoven's Ninth Symphony playing through a cymatic device."},{"time":170000,"text":"So it kind of flips things on its head a little bit."},{"time":173000,"text":"This is Pink Floyd's \"Machine\""},{"time":175000,"text":"playing in real time through the cymascope."},{"time":183000,"text":"We can also use cymatics as a looking glass into nature."},{"time":186000,"text":"And we can actually recreate the archetypal forms of nature."},{"time":189000,"text":"So, for example, here on the left we can see a snowflake as it would appear in nature."},{"time":193000,"text":"Then on the right we can see a cymatically created snowflake."},{"time":196000,"text":"And here is a starfish and a cymatic starfish."},{"time":198000,"text":"And there is thousands of these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"So what does this all mean?"},{"time":202000,"text":"Well, there is still a lot to explore"},{"time":205000,"text":"in its early days. And there's not many people working in this field."},{"time":207000,"text":"But consider for a moment that sound does have form."},{"time":211000,"text":"We've seen that it can affect matter and cause form within matter."},{"time":215000,"text":"Then sort of take a leap and think about the universe forming."},{"time":219000,"text":"And think about the immense sound of the universe forming."},{"time":222000,"text":"And if we kind of ponder on that, then perhaps"},{"time":224000,"text":"cymatics had an influence on the formation of the universe itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"And here is some eye candy for you, from a range of"},{"time":231000,"text":"DIY scientists and artists"},{"time":233000,"text":"from all over the globe."},{"time":235000,"text":"Cymatics is accessible to everybody."},{"time":237000,"text":"I want to urge everybody here to"},{"time":239000,"text":"apply your passion, your knowledge"},{"time":242000,"text":"and your skills to areas like cymatics."},{"time":244000,"text":"I think collectively we can build a global community."},{"time":247000,"text":"We can inspire each other."},{"time":249000,"text":"And we can evolve this exploration"},{"time":251000,"text":"of the substance of things not seen. Thank you."},{"time":253000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}